Explanation:

We use nested for loops to iterate through the array nums twice, once for each element. For each pair of elements, we calculate their XOR value and check if it falls within the given range (low and high). If it does, we increment the count. The time complexity is O(n^2) because of the nested loops, where n is the array length. The space complexity is O(n) because we only use a single integer variable to store the count. The energy implications are low because the algorithm performs simple arithmetic operations and does not require any complex calculations or data structures.

